  "text": "The log segment and index architecture in apache/kafka is primarily in storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/. Key files: LogSegment.java is the core segment class; LogSegments.java manages the collection of segments; AbstractIndex.java is the base for all index types; OffsetIndex.java and TimeIndex.java implement offset-to-position and time-to-offset index file formats; TransactionIndex.java tracks aborted transactions per segment; LogConfig.java holds topic/log-level configuration and validation; LogLoader.java handles log recovery on startup (rebuilding indexes, truncating corrupt segments); LogManager.java orchestrates log directory management and recovery-point checkpointing; LocalLog.java manages the append path with segments; UnifiedLog.java is the top-level log abstraction. For checkpoint-based recovery: OffsetCheckpointFile.java and CheckpointFileWithFailureHandler.java (in the checkpoint package) wrap CheckpointFile.java (in server-common) to persist recovery-point offsets to disk.",
